title.narrative: NUTRITION:HEALTH, NUTRITION AND Early Child Development (ECD) SYSTEMS

description.narrative: Health and school systems have enhanced capacities to prevent child and adolescent malnutrition, including obesity., which contributes to Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, children benefit from quality, evidence-based and integrated health, nutrition and early childhood development systems

title.narrative: Health and school systems have enhanced capacities to prevent child and adolescent malnutrition, including obesity.

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF continued to support;six maternity wards in Republika Srpska to complete;accreditation in accordance with Standards for Baby-Friendly Hospitals in order to have 100% of maternity wards accredited in RS. The accreditation process has become self-sustainable in the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina (FBiH). The sixth phase of theNutrition-friendly Schools/Preschools;Initiativewas continued, reaching 2,000 kindergarten children and 1,000 school age children. Breastfeeding trainings for pediatricians and gynecologists were conducted in 10 municipalities, reaching 71 professionals. More than 10,000 services in infant and young child feeding were provided to refugee and migrant children and their families. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/01/2022
